2. Personnel who are assigned the responsibility of operating the ARV shall complete
training approved by BNPD.
3, Only authorized department personnel shall drive the ARV. All such operators shall
have completed the training as required within this policy. All personnel shall follow
departmental policy during the ARV’s operation.
Training curriculum must be approved by the Chief of Police. All department
training shall consist of classroom and practical hands-on training within the
following specified topics:
a.
b.
Overview of the ARV to include its capabilities and limitations;
Characteristics of the ARV so operators will maintain detailed knowledge of the
unit’s size and weight;
Basic maintenance;
Safe operating speeds;
Effective methods for the proper maneuvering and steering of the ARV;
Ground guiding techniques for the safe operation of the ARV in areas containing
diminished visibility;
Operation of the ARV on slopes, grades, and hills;
Restricted terrain;
Operating the ARV on rough or uneven terrain features;
Specific information relating to the ARV’s propensity for rollover;
Danger areas that could result in falls, smashes, or pinched extremities;
ARV egress procedures during rollovers;
. The use of seat belts: and
The risks associated with contacting high voltage power lines.
